<h1>The Abjad <_LeafSpannerInterface> class</h1>

<subsection>

<p>
The Abjad <_LeafSpannerInterface> class models the functionality that all leaf interfaces share.
</p>

</subsection>

<interface>
<methods>
   <local> append( )
   <local> die( )
   <local> find( )
   <local> first( )
   <local> fracture( )
   <local> fuse( )
   <local> get( )
   <local> last( )
</methods>
<overloads>
   <local> __contains__
   <local> __getitem__
   <local> __len__
</overloads>
</interface>

<comments>

<p>
The Abajad <_LeafSpannerInterface> class instantiates automatically at leaf-initialization time.
</p>

<p>
The <_LeafSpannerInterface> gives you access to all the spanners associated with a particular <code>_Leaf</code> instance. 
Through this interface one can <code>get</code> spanners, kill (<code>die( )</code>) spanners, split (<code>fracture( )</code>) spanners, <code>fuse</code> spanners and perform queries. 
</p>

</comments>

